      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">6.206</ph>
         <ph rev="FAC 2024-03 February 9, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022-009?>Set-asides for service-disabled veteran-owned small business (SDVOSB) concerns eligible under the SDVOSB Program.<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 6.206 by—   a.  Revising the section heading; ?></ph>
      </title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d373e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d387e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> To fulfill the statutory requirements relating to the Veterans Benefits Act of2003 (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.657f</xref>), contracting officers may set-aside solicitations to allow only service-disabled veteran-owned <ph rev="FAC 2024-03 February 9, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber]  FAR Case 2022-009?>small business concerns eligible under the SDVOSB Program<?FM MARKER [Why] b.  Removing from paragraph (a) “small business concerns” and adding “small business concerns eligible under the SDVOSB Program” in its place; and?></ph> to compete (see <xref href="19.1405.dita#FAR_19_1405"
                        base="i1099446"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1405</xref>).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d387e21">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> No separate justification or determination and findings are required under this part to set aside a contract action for service-disabled veteran-owned <ph rev="FAC 2024-03 February 9, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber]  FAR Case 2022-009?>small business concerns eligible under the SDVOSB Program<?FM MARKER [Why] c.  Removing from paragraph (b) “small business concerns” and adding “small business concerns eligible under the SDVOSB Program” in its place.?></ph>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
